r base in crypto, and define user experiences for entirely new features that the ecosystem has not seen before. What you\u2019ll be doing Work in a small team to iteratively improve user experience Take new features from ideation, to prototyping, to user testing, to production Design web and mobile experiences that are simple and intuitive Participate in regular design reviews where you\u2019ll seek out specific feedback on your designs and incorporate relevant feedback Execute on the product roadmap and help define product strategy Daily collaboration with Engineering, User Research, and Product What we look for in you 5+ years of professional Product Design experience Experience designing consumer-facing experiences for web and mobile Excellence in UX thinking, visual design, and written communication Experience working in a collaborative environment with engineers, user researchers, and product teams Fluency in Figma and prototyping tools Comfort in a fast paced, iterative, experimental, and data-driven environment Understanding of acquisition and conversion, metrics-driven design, and eg. A/B experimentation Strong interest in crypto consumer customer life cycle Lots of empathy for customers ie. business success through the lens of user success Low ego, collaborative, and open minded Nice to haves Interest in crypto or financial products User of Coinbase products Coinbase is committed to diversity in its workforce and is proud to be an equal opportunity employer and to review all of our job postings to minimize biased language. Coinbase does not make hiring or employment decisions on the basis of race, color, religion, creed, gender, national origin, age, disability, veteran status, marital status, pregnancy, sex, gender expression or identity, sexual orientation, citizenship, or any other basis protected by applicable local, state or federal law. Coinbase will also consider for employment qualified applicants with arrest and conviction records in a manner consi